// Recycler View -- Traffic Rules While driving always carry your driving license and important documents such as your vehicle registration certificate. MUST NOT carry more than one pillion rider and he/she MUST sit astride the machine on a proper seat and should keep both feet on the footrests. You should be aware of what is behind and in the sides before maneuvering. Look behind you; use mirrors if they are fitted. Never Drink while driving. Follow the traffic signals, lights and signs. Avoid using the cell phone when driving. If urgent move to left, stop and then take the call. Always use a helmet. Do not ride or wheel your vehicle on to the footpath. Understand the signals given by other road users and use the same when riding. Never stop abruptly in traffic. Move to the left and slow down. MUST wear a protective helmet. Helmets MUST comply with the Regulations and they MUST be fastened securely. Dont sit children on fuel tanks or stand them in front of the rider. Dangerous Curse To Left Road Sign.
